cytoscape.hyperedge.impl
Class HyperEdgeImpl

java.lang.Object
  cytoscape.hyperedge.impl.HyperEdgeImpl
All Implemented Interfaces:
HyperEdge, Identifiable, Matchable
public class HyperEdgeImpl
extends java.lang.Object
implements HyperEdge

Implementation of the HyperEdge interface.

Unmodifiable Iterator Return Values

Several HyperEdge operations return unmodifiable iterators as return values (e.g., HyperEdge.getEdges()). Creation of all these iterators is done using HEUtils.buildUnmodifiableCollectionIterator(). These iterators have certain properties that should be understood. Please see this method for details.

Version:
1.1
Author:
Michael L. Creech

public boolean addToNetwork(cytoscape.CyNetwork net)
Description copied from interface: HyperEdge
Add a given HyperEdge to a given CyNetwork. Only a HyperEdge that doesn't connect to another HyperEdge can be added to another CyNetwork. All CyNodes and CyEdges contained within this HyperEdge will be added to the target CyNetwork.

Specified by:
addToNetwork in interface HyperEdge
Parameters:
net - the CyNetwork that will be modified to contain the CyNodes and CyEdges contained in this HyperEdge.
Returns:
true if this HyperEdge was newly added to net. false if net is null, if this HyperEdge is aleady a member of net, or if this HyperEdge shares any edges with another HyperEdge (via connectHyperEdge()).

If this HyperEdge is successfully added to net, all HyperEdgeManager ChangeListeners are notified by invoking each listener's objectChanged() method with an EventNote of type HYPEREDGE, sub-type=ADDED and a supporting information object being net.

removeFromNetwork

public boolean removeFromNetwork(cytoscape.CyNetwork net)
Description copied from interface: HyperEdge
Remove this HyperEdge from a given CyNetwork. The CyEdges of this HyperEdge will be removed from this CyNetwork. Under certain conditions, the ConnectorNode of this HyperEdge will also be removed (see destroy() for details). CyNodes are never removed, since it is difficult to tell if the CyNodes existed prior to the creation of the HyperEdge.

Specified by:
removeFromNetwork in interface HyperEdge
Parameters:
net - the CyNetwork from which to remove this HyperEdge. If null, will remove this HyperEdge from all CyNetworks for which this HyperEdge belongs (equivalent to destroy()).
Returns:
true if this HyperEdge was removed from net. false if this HyperEdge was not a member of net.

Before this HyperEdge is successfully removed from net, one of two event notifications are fired:

  1. If net is null, or is the last CyNetwork to which this HyperEdge belongs, the HyperEdge will be deleted and all the HyperEdgeManager's DeleteListeners are notified this HyperEdge is deleted (see DeleteListener.objectDestroyed()).
  2. If net is not null and is not the last CyNetwork to which this HyperEdge belongs, all the HyperEdgeManager's ChangeListeners are notified by invoking each listener's objectChanged() method with an EventNote of type HYPEREDGE, sub-type=REMOVED and a supporting information object being net.

removeFromNetworkBookkeeping

protected void removeFromNetworkBookkeeping(cytoscape.CyNetwork net,
                                            java.util.Set<giny.model.GraphObject> toIgnoreForDeletion)
This method is similar to removeFromNetwork() but will not actually hide nodes and edges found within a given Set. This is used for Cytoscape node and edge removals that trigger needed updates to HyperEdges. This is because these nodes and edges are in the process of being deleted. NOTE: This method may be removed if (when) HyperEdge is placed in the Cytoscape core. Calls to this method would be replaced with removeFromNetwork().

removeNode

public boolean removeNode(cytoscape.CyNode node)
Description copied from interface: HyperEdge
Remove all CyEdges associated with a given CyNode from this HyperEdge. This may cause this entire HyperEdge to be removed if the number of CyEdges falls below getMinimumNumberEdges (see destroy() for details).

Based on the above situations, one of two event notifications may be fired:

  1. If removal of the CyNode leads to this HyperEdge being deleted, then before this HyperEdge is deleted, all HyperEdgeManger DeleteListeners are notified that this HyperEdge is being deleted (see DeleteListener.objectDestroyed()).
  2. If removal of the CyNode does not lead to this HyperEdge being deleted, then before each CyEdge is removed, all HyperEdgeManager ChangeListeners are notified by invoking each listener's objectChanged() method with an EventNote of type EDGE, sub-type=REMOVED and a supporting information object=the removed edge (see ChangeListener.objectChanged()). Note that multiple objectChanged() notifications may take place--one for each CyEdge associated with node.

Specified by:
removeNode in interface HyperEdge
Parameters:
node - the CyNode to remove.
Returns:
true if the node was removed, false if the node is not found, or is null.

removeEdge

public boolean removeEdge(cytoscape.CyEdge edge)
Description copied from interface: HyperEdge
Remove the given CyEdge from this HyperEdge. If the CyNode associated with this CyEdge is not connected to any other CyEdges, then this CyNode will be removed from this HyperEdge. Removal of this CyEdge will cause this entire HyperEdge to be removed if the number of CyEdges falls below getMinimumNumberEdges (see destroy() for details).

Based on the above situations, one of two event notifications may be fired:

  1. If removal of the CyEdge leads to this HyperEdge being deleted then before this HyperEdge is deleted, all HyperEdgeManger DeleteListeners are notified that this HyperEdge is being deleted (see DeleteListener.objectDestroyed()).
  2. If removal of the CyEdge does not lead to this HyperEdge being deleted, then before this this CyEdge is removed, all HyperEdgeManager ChangeListeners are notified by invoking each listener's objectChanged() method with an EventNote of type EDGE, sub-type=REMOVED and a supporting information object=the removed edge (see ChangeListener.objectChanged()).

Specified by:
removeEdge in interface HyperEdge
Parameters:
edge - the CyEdge to remove.
Returns:
true if the edge was removed, false if edge is null or is not a member of this HyperEdge.

                                     cytoscape.CyNetwork net,

addEdge

public cytoscape.CyEdge addEdge(cytoscape.CyNode node,
                                java.lang.String edgeIType)
Description copied from interface: HyperEdge
Add a new CyEdge connecting a given CyNode to this HyperEdge and to all CyNetworks to which this HyperEdge belongs.

Under the appropriate conditions (see ChangeListener.objectChanged()) and after the CyEdge is added, all of the HyperEdgeManager's ChangeListeners are notified by invoking their objectChanged() method with an EventNote of type EDGE, sub-type=ADDED and a supporting information object=the new CyEdge.

Specified by:
addEdge in interface HyperEdge
Parameters:
node - the CyNode for which to add a new CyEdge. If node is not a member of this HyperEdge, it will be added. If node is already a member of this HyperEdge, and edgeIType is different then the interaction type of all existing CyEdges to node, another CyEdge will be created that is attached to node with the given edgeIType. If a CyEdge is found that attaches to node and has the same edgeIType, an exception will be thrown.
edgeIType - the interaction type of the CyEdge to create. edgeIType also determines the Role played by the node within the newly created CyEdge. This is done by using edgeIType as a key in the EdgeTypeMap to determine the EdgeRole associated with that edgeIType. If the value associated with the edgeIType key is EdgeRole.SOURCE, then node will be the source of the newly created CyEdge. If the value associated with the edgeIType key is EdgeRole.TARGET, then node will be the target of the newly created CyEdge. If edgeIType is not the key for any EdgeRole in the EdgeTypeMap, then node is used as the source of the newly created CyEdge.
Returns:
the newly created CyEdge that was added to all CyNetworks to which this HyperEdge belongs.

connectHyperEdges

public cytoscape.CyEdge connectHyperEdges(HyperEdge targetHE,
                                          java.lang.String edgeIType)
Description copied from interface: HyperEdge
Connect this HyperEdge to another. Adds a CyEdge that is shared in between this HyperEdge and a given target HyperEdge. The CyEdge connects the two HyperEdge's ConnectorNodes. Note that once two HyperEdges are connected, they can only exist in at most one CyNetwork (addToCyNetwork() will throw an exception). If an edge connection already exists in between this HyperEdge and the given target HyperEdge, that contains the given CyEdge interaction types, it will simply be returned.

Specified by:
connectHyperEdges in interface HyperEdge
Parameters:
targetHE - the target HyperEdge to connect to. Must be a member of exactly the same one CyNetwork as this HyperEdge.
edgeIType - the interaction type of the CyEdge within this HyperEdge and targetHE.

copy

public java.util.Map<HyperEdge,HyperEdge> copy(cytoscape.CyNetwork net,
                                               EdgeFilter filter)
Description copied from interface: HyperEdge
Copy this HyperEdge into a new HyperEdge and place it in the specified CyNetwork. The copy will include copies of all CyEdges of this HyperEdge that pass the given EdgeFilter. All attributes associated with this HyperEdge's ConnectorNode and the copied edges are copied.

Specified by:
copy in interface HyperEdge
Parameters:
net - the CyNetwork into which to place the copied HyperEdge.
filter - the EdgeFilter to apply to each CyEdge of this HyperEdge. Only Edges that pass the EdgeFilter are included in the copy. If an Edge is a shared edge, the connected HyperEdge is also copied with the EdgeFilter being applied to each of the connected HyperEdge's CyEdges. Example: 
 he1.copy (net , new EdgeFilter () {
            boolean includeEdge (HyperEdge he, CyEdge edge) { return true; }
        });
would copy all edges. For some common examples, see EdgeFilters.
Returns:
a non-null Map with keys being the HyperEdges to copy and values being the corresponding copied HyperEdges. If filter excludes shared edges, or if this HyperEdge has no shared edges, then the Map will contain one element--this HyperEdge as the key with a copy of this HyperEdge as the value.
See Also:
HyperEdge.getMinimumNumberEdges(), EdgeFilters

destroy

public void destroy()
Description copied from interface: HyperEdge
Remove this HyperEdge. All CyEdges belonging to this HyperEdge will be removed from Cytoscape. The ConnectorNode of this HyperEdge is also removed unless "regular" (non-HyperEdge) edges are connected to the ConnectorNode. In this case, the ConnectorNode is removed from all CyNetworks that do not have such edges. All automatically generated attributes of the ConnectorNode and all CyEdges are also removed. The LifeState of this HyperEdge is set to DELETED and any future attempts to perform operations on this object will throw IllegalStateExceptions.

Before this HyperEdge is deleted, DeleteListener.objectDestroyed() methods are invoked to notify interested listeners that this object is being destroyed.

Specified by:
destroy in interface HyperEdge
